data.text:
About Nancy Ajram

Nancy Ajram is an iconic Lebanese pop singer known for a collection of hits, including Ah W Noss, Atabtab and Ya Kether. Throughout her career, she has sold several millions of albums across the globe. She is regarded as one of the most successful and influential Middle Eastern recording artists.

Personal Life

She married Fadi El Hachem in 2008. The couple had their first child, Mila in 2009. Their second child Ella was born in 2011.

Awards

She has earned numerous awards throughout her career, including multiple World Music Awards and Murex D'or Awards.

Trivia

Oprah Winfrey once described her as the Middle East's Britney Spears.
